{
  "version": 2,
  "name": "Text",
  "description": "Text generator — decomposed from the legacy `TextGenerator` Rust struct into a single-primitive JSON graph.\n\nThe preset is the smallest possible shape: `system.generator_input → node.render_text → system.final_output`. All scalar outer-card params (size / position_x / position_y / scale / h_align / v_align / letter_spacing / line_spacing) bind 1:1 to `node.render_text`'s matching ports — port-shadows-param, so wiring an LFO or envelope through the graph editor animates them. The two string params (text + fontFamily) flow through `stringBindings` into the primitive's String ParamDefs, the same shape `node.image_folder.folder` is driven from the MriVolume preset.\n\nThe glyph rasterizer lives entirely inside `node.render_text` (CoreText → R8Unorm bitmap, dirty-cached) and the composite shader writes white-on-black into the output with aspect correction. Per-clip overrides for text + fontFamily flow through `Clip.string_params` the same way they did on the legacy Rust generator — one preset, any clip can re-point at different text or a different font.",
